Key Match Events: Kristaps Porzingis returned from an ankle sprain and recorded 11 points, five rebounds, two assists, and two blocks in the Boston Celtics' 109-86 win over the Houston Rockets.
Porzingis' rim protection and two blocks were crucial to the Celtics' defensive success.
Post-Match Reflections: After the game, Porzingis discussed the challenge of returning from his injury.
Head coach Joe Mazzulla acknowledged the difficulty of returning from injury but praised Porzingis' defense.
